'''Kristaps Porziņģis''' ({{IPA-lv|ˈkris.taps ˈpuɔr.ziɲ.ɟis}}; born 2 August 1995) is a Latvian professional [[basketball]] player for the [[Dallas Mavericks]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA). He is the [[List of tallest players in National Basketball Association history|one of the tallest active players]] in the NBA, standing at {{height|ft=7|in=3}} tall, and plays both the [[Power forward (basketball)|power forward]] and [[Center (basketball)|center]] positions.

Born in [[Liepāja]], Porziņģis began his professional career with [[EuroLeague]] team [[CB Sevilla|Sevilla]] in 2011. Porziņģis quickly rose through the team's youth ranks and became the figurehead of the senior team by 2013. He subsequently won the [[EuroCup Basketball Rising Star]] award in 2015, where, at age 18, he became the youngest ever recipient of the award. The following summer, he declared for the [[NBA draft]], where he was selected fourth overall by the [[New York Knicks]]. 

In New York, Porziņģis shone as the team's star, but after disagreements with the front office, was traded to Dallas in 2019.

==Early career==
Porziņģis followed his parents' footsteps and started to play basketball at age 6. Once he turned 12, his older brother, [[Jānis Porziņģis|Jānis]], who played professionally in Europe, would take him to offseason training sessions.<ref>{{cite news |last1= Begley| first1= Ian|title=Big brothers are watching Kristaps Porzingis and it's paying off| url= http://espn.go.com/nba/story/_/id/14373136/nba-kristaps-porzingis-owes-success-basketball-life-family| accessdate=15 December 2015 |work=ESPN.com|date=15 December 2015}}</ref> He played in youth competition with [[BK Liepājas Lauvas]], the most famous club based in hometown of [[Liepāja]], until he was 15 years old. An agent from Latvia sent video of him around this time to teams in Spain and Italy.<ref name= eurocup /> In 2010, [[CB Sevilla|Baloncesto Sevilla]], a club that had a professional team competing in the [[Liga ACB]] in Spain, called Porziņģis for a tryout in an attempt to recruit foreign talent to its junior squads. He stood {{cvt|6|ft|8|in}} and weighed {{cvt|157|lb}} at this time.<ref name= eurocup>{{cite web| url= http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/features/player-spotlight/i/141583|title=Kristaps Porzingis, Baloncesto Seville |work= Eurocupbasketball.com|accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref><ref name= draftexpress>{{cite web|title=Kristaps Porzingis|url=http://www.draftexpress.com/profile/Kristaps-Porzingis-7119/|website=Draft Express|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> Porziņģis recalled the moment and said, "I came here with my brother for two or three days, but it was really hot and I couldn't play at my best because of that. Still, I received a contract in summer 2010 and I signed it."<ref name=eurocup /> Inmaculada Avivar, a nutritionist for Sevilla, diagnosed that Porziņģis was suffering from [[anemia]], meaning that he had fewer [[red blood cell]]s.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anemia|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/anemia|website=Merriam-Webster: Dictionary and Thesaurus|accessdate=7 July 2014}}</ref> This caused him to feel fatigue, shortness of breath, and inability to exercise. Nevertheless, he gradually overcame the condition and began seeing improvement in his game.<ref name=eurocup /> In addition to his medical problems, Porziņģis had trouble picking up the [[Spanish language|language]] in [[Seville]], making him reluctant to return there after his first tryout. In his first season playing for the junior squad, he struggled to communicate with the coaching staff and his teammates and was often sleepy due to his health.<ref name=eurocup />

Porziņģis debuted for the youth squad on 4 January 2012, against its counterpart from [[FC Barcelona Bàsquet|Barcelona]], adding 12 points and 10 rebounds. The opposing side was led by Alexander Zhigulin, who would go on to enter the [[2015 NBA draft]] and withdraw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alexandr Zhigulin Player Profile|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Alexandr-Zhigulin/Summary/25104|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> However, Sevilla was defeated, 56–75.<ref>{{cite web|title=FC Barcelona Regal Junior Team 75,  Cajasol Seville Junior Team 56|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2012-01-04/FC-Barcelona-Regal-Junior-Team-at-Cajasol-Seville-Junior-Team/87361|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> This game was part of the Ciutat de L'Hospitalet tournament, which led up to the [[Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament|Nike International Junior Tournament]] (NIJT).<ref name=eurocup /> On 5 January, he scored a personal best of 16 points on the [[OKK Spars Sarajevo|Spars Sarajevo]] youth squad, helping Sevilla beat their opponents by a margin of 8 points.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cajasol Seville Junior Team 80,  KK Spars Junior Team 72|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2012-01-05/Cajasol-Seville-Junior-Team-at-KK-Spars-Junior-Team/87369|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> Porziņģis said, "I knew it was a prestigious tournament and that I had to do well", he said. "I think I could have done much better, but I wasn't physically 100 percent. I have seen videos and could have been much more aggressive. But I wish I could have played better."<ref name=eurocup /> He finished the tournament averaging 9.2 points, 4.8 rebounds and 2.6 blocks.<ref name=eurocup /> Porziņģis represented the Sevilla junior team again at the same tournament in early 2013. Against [[KK Olimpija|Union Olimpija]] on 4 January, he recorded 15 points and 6 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Union Olimpija Junior Team 70,  Cajasol Seville Junior Team 78|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2013-01-04/Union-Olimpija-Junior-Team-at-Cajasol-Seville-Junior-Team/120276|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> On 6 January, in the team's tournament finale vs [[Real Madrid Baloncesto B|Real Madrid]]'s youth squad, he scored 24 points and grabbed 11 rebounds. He also made a total of five three-pointers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cajasol Seville Junior Team 66,  Real Madrid Junior Team 72|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2013-01-06/Cajasol-Seville-Junior-Team-at-Real-Madrid-Junior-Team/120286|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> Porziņģis proved to be more effective in his second year, averaging 16.6 points, 8.4 rebounds and 2.6 blocks and going .481 on three-pointers.<ref name=eurocup /> This would be his final stint in the youth categories of Sevilla.

==Professional career==
===Sevilla===
====2012–13: Rookie season====
Entering the [[2012–13 ACB season]], Sevilla had hired [[Aíto García Reneses]], who previously worked with the likes of [[Pau Gasol]], [[Juan Carlos Navarro (basketball)|Juan Carlos Navarro]], [[Ricky Rubio]] and [[Rudy Fernández (basketball)|Rudy Fernández]].<ref name=eurocup /> On 29 September 2012, Porziņģis got the opportunity to make an appearance with the club's first team, but was allowed to play just a minute. Sevilla took a tremendous loss to [[CB Murcia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Universidad Católica De Murcia CB 93,  Baloncesto Sevilla 77|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2012-09-29/Universidad-Catolica-De-Murcia-CB-at-Baloncesto-Sevilla/103535|website=[[RealGM]]|access-date=20 June 2015}}</ref> Following a return to the youth categories of the club at the Torneig de Bàsquet Junior Ciutat de L'Hospitalet, he went back to competing for the senior squad. On 16 January 2013, he logged only four minutes against [[BC Spartak Saint Petersburg|Spartak Saint Petersburg]] in the [[EuroCup Basketball|EuroCup]], scoring no points, but contributing one rebound and one assist.<ref>{{cite web|title=Baloncesto Sevilla 59, Spartak Saint Petersburg 78|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2013-01-16/Baloncesto-Sevilla-at-Spartak-Saint-Petersburg/119941|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref> He scored his first basket for the senior team on 20 February 2013, in a rematch with Spartak. Porziņģis said, "I was very nervous at the beginning: I wanted to do well and not pick up turnovers. At the same time, I got a lot of confidence with players of my same age. That allowed me to play better with the first team and practice with more confidence."<ref name=eurocup /> On 4 May 2013, he posted a season-high 7 points with the senior team, hitting two of three shots vs [[Bilbao Basket]] in [[Liga ACB|ACB]] competition.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bilbao Basket 81, Baloncesto Sevilla 60|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2013-05-04/Bilbao-Basket-at-Baloncesto-Sevilla/103817|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref>

====2013–14: Second season and NBA consideration====
Porziņģis opened his second season on Sevilla's main squad strong in his third game against the [[EuroLeague]] team [[Saski Baskonia|Laboral Kutxa]], leading them to a 20-point ACB victory on 2 November 2013.<ref name=eurocup /> He notched a career-high 12 points, 6 rebounds, and 4 blocks.<ref name=second>{{cite web|title=2013–2014 International Games|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Kristaps-Porzingis/GameLogs/32861/International/2014|website=[[RealGM]]|access-date=22 June 2015}}</ref> He broke his scoring record once more against [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] on 30 November 2013, nearly leading his team to a victory.<ref name=eurocup /><ref name=second /> Against the very same team on 6 April 2014, Porziņģis scored a career-high 20 points, nailing 2 three-pointers.<ref name=second /> Despite his team losing, he began to trend on social media because of his performance. He said, "It was a very good game for me on offense. I didn't get any rebounds in that game. I had a good shooting night, but could have helped more on defense. Still, fans in Madrid gave me a nice ovation when I fouled out and I liked that a lot."<ref name="eurocup" /> On 25 May, he got the chance to face his idol [[Justin Doellman]] of Barcelona, whom he called the "best power forward in Spanish basketball". He scored 14 points against Doellman's team.<ref name=eurocup /><ref name="second" /> In May 2014, Porziņģis was selected in the [[ACB Best Young Player Award|ACB All-Young Players Team]] of the [[2013–14 ACB season|2013–14 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acb.com/redaccion.php?id=103864|title=2013–14 ACB All-Young players Team|date=20 May 2014|publisher=ACB.com|language=Spanish|access-date=2 June 2014}}</ref>

In April, Porziņģis declared himself eligible for the [[2014 NBA draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diena.lv/sports/basketbols/porzingis-tomer-pieteicies-nba-draftam-14053842|title=Porziņģis tomēr pieteicies NBA draftam|date=28 April 2014|publisher=Diena.lv|language=Latvian|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> Before and after he made the decision, he drew interest from [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) teams such as the [[Orlando Magic]], who held the 12th overall pick, and traveled to Europe to scout him. The [[Oklahoma City Thunder]] reportedly were certainly going to select him with the 21st pick in the case that he remained. Porziņģis was considered an unfinished product and a top-15 draft pick. According to DraftExpress.com, he was the fourth-youngest prospect in their top-100 rankings.<ref name=draftexpress /><ref>{{cite web|last1=Herbert|first1=James|title=NBA Draft 2014: Latvian prospect Kristaps Porzingis to enter draft|url=https://www.sbnation.com/nba/2014/4/28/5660788/kristaps-porzingis-nba-draft|website=SB Nation|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> Shortly before the day of the draft, however, he withdrew his name. Porziņģis's [[sports agent|agent]] Andy Miller released the information to [[ESPN]], saying that his client did not feel prepared to become a part of the NBA and wanted to develop his skills until the [[2015 NBA draft|2015 draft]]. One of the league's general managers commented on him, "He's very talented. He wasn't ready, but we would've seriously considered drafting him anyway. If he continues to develop his game, get more minutes and his body develops, I think he could be a top-five pick in 2015. He has that kind of talent."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ford|first1=Chad|title=Kristaps Porzingis pulls out of draft|url=http://espn.go.com/nba/draft2014/story/_/id/11090062/2014-nba-draft-kristaps-porzingis-latvia-pulls-draft|website=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref>

====2014–15: EuroCup Rising Star====
Prior to the [[2014–15 ACB season]], head coach Aíto García Reneses parted ways with Sevilla.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coach Aito Reneses leaves Cajasol Sevilla|url=http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/spain/126153/coach-aito-reneses-leaves-cajasol-sevilla.html|website=Sportando.com|access-date=22 June 2015}}</ref> On 4 October 2014, against [[CB 1939 Canarias]], Porziņģis made his season debut in the Liga ACB, scoring 3 points in the game. He made his first appearance at the [[2014–15 Eurocup Basketball|2014–15 EuroCup]] on 15 October, vs. [[EWE Baskets Oldenburg]] and scored 2 points. However, he had a strong EuroCup performance against [[Pallacanestro Virtus Roma]] in the weeks that followed, in which he contributed 18 points, 7 rebounds, 4 assists, 4 steals and 2 blocks. He recorded a double-double in mid-November in a win over [[CB Estudiantes|Estudiantes]], adding 11 points and 11 rebounds. On 11 February 2015, he scored a season-high 19 points against the EuroCup's [[Turów Zgorzelec]]. He tied this record on 18 April 2015, vs. [[Bàsquet Manresa]] in the ACB.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014–2015 International Games|url=http://basketball.realgm.com/player/Kristaps-Porzingis/GameLogs/32861|website=[[RealGM]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> On 15 April 2015, Porziņģis was named the winner of the [[EuroCup Basketball Rising Star|EuroCup Rising Star]] Award of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/news/i/5vvspvb5hnnlj9ye|title=2014–15 Eurocup Rising Star Trophy winner: Kristaps Porzingis, Baloncesto Seville|publisher=Eurocupbasketball.com|accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref> One month later, he repeated in the ACB All-Young Players Team, after avoiding the [[promotion and relegation|relegation]] with Baloncesto Sevilla.<ref>[http://www.acb.com/redaccion.php?id=113351 Mejor Quinteto Joven de la Liga Endesa 2014–15]; ACB.com, 19 May 2015</ref>

===New York Knicks===
On 16 April 2015, Porziņģis entered the [[2015 NBA draft]], according to a report from agent Andy Miller.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nba/draft2015/story/_/id/12698126/latvian-power-forward-kristaps-porzingis-declare-nba-draft|title=Latvian power forward Kristaps Porzingis to enter draft|date=16 April 2015|publisher=ESPN.com|accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref> After gaining a season more of experience, he became known as a [[NBA draft lottery|lottery]] pick and a potential top-5 selection. He drew interest from teams such as the [[Los Angeles Lakers]], who had the No. 2 pick and had several personnel that had seen Porziņģis play in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ding|first1=Kevin|title=Mystery Man Kristaps Porzingis Tempts Many in NBA Draft, but Will Any Team Bite?|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2503065-mystery-man-kristaps-porzingis-tempts-many-in-nba-draft-but-will-any-team-bite|website=[[Bleacher Report]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> He was compared with players such as [[Pau Gasol]] and [[Dirk Nowitzki]], but also [[Darko Miličić]], a former lottery selection widely considered a [[draft bust]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Murphy|first1=David|title=Why Kristaps Porzingis Could Be the Shocker of the 2015 NBA Draft Class|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2500096-why-kristaps-porzingis-could-be-the-shocker-of-the-2015-nba-draft-class|website=[[Bleacher Report]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> Adrian Wojnarowski of [[Yahoo! Sports]] wrote, "Porziņģis has an innate awareness about the way the American public sees a young, long European teenager. He comes to the NBA with the full understanding that popular basketball culture declares him guilty until proven innocent of the basketball crimes of [[Darko Miličić]] and [[Nikoloz Tskitishvili]] and [[Andrea Bargnani]]. He's considered a stiff, a bust, a blown lottery pick until he doesn't become one..."<ref name=prodigy>{{cite web|last1=Wojnarowski|first1=Adrian|title=Meet the Euro prodigy who seems unlike the flops who came before him|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/meet-the-euro-prodigy-who-seems-unlike-the-flops-who-came-before-him-193427860.html|website=[[Yahoo! Sports]]|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref>

On 25 June 2015, Porziņģis was selected with the fourth overall pick in the [[2015 NBA draft]] by the [[New York Knicks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/knicks/draft/no.-4-pick-knicks-select|title=With The No. 4 Pick, The Knicks Select Kristaps Porzingis|date=25 June 2015|work=NBA.com|accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Berman|first1=Marc|title=Knicks take Euro stud Kristaps Porziņģis with No. 4 pick|url=https://nypost.com/2015/06/25/knicks-take-euro-stud-kristaps-porzingis-with-no-4-pick/|accessdate=26 June 2015|work=nypost.com|date=26 June 2015}}</ref> He was booed by some New York fans upon being drafted, but vowed to change the fans' opinions on him from negative to positive.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://nypost.com/2015/06/25/why-knicks-fans-at-draft-were-so-upset-with-porzingis-pick/ | work=New York Post | first=George | last=Willis | title=Why Knicks fans at draft booed Porzingis pick | date=26 June 2015}}</ref> On the same night, the New York Knicks traded for Porziņģis' teammate from Sevilla, [[Willy Hernangómez]], who was originally drafted by the [[Philadelphia 76ers]] as a 35th overall pick.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Carey|first1=Matt|title=Sixers Draft Guillermo Hernangomez With Pick #35, Trade Him To Knicks For Two Future Picks|url=http://www.libertyballers.com/2015/6/25/8849409/sixers-draft-Hernangomez-with-pick-35-trade-him-immediately|accessdate=26 June 2015|work=libertyballers.com|date=25 June 2015}}</ref> Porziņģis became the highest drafted Latvian and Baltic player in NBA history.

====2015–16: Rookie season====
[[File:Kristaps Porzingis and Kris Humphries.jpg|thumb|Porziņģis on 31 October 2015, in his third NBA game]]
On 30 July 2015, Porziņģis signed his rookie-scale contract with the Knicks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/knicks/knicks-sign-kristaps-porzingis-and-jerian-grant|title=Knicks Sign Kristaps Porzingis and Jerian Grant|work=NBA.com|date=30 July 2015|accessdate=30 July 2015}}</ref> On 28 October 2015, he scored 16 points in his NBA debut, leading New York to a 122–97 season-opening win over the [[Milwaukee Bucks]]. He was 3 of 11 from the field and 9 of 12 from the line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151028/NYKMIL/gameinfo.html|title=Williams scores 24, Knicks beat Bucks 122–97 in opener|work=NBA.com|date=28 October 2015|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref> On 21 November 2015, he had 24 points, 14 rebounds and seven blocked shots to lead the Knicks to a 107–102 victory over the [[Houston Rockets]], becoming the first 20-year-old to post such a stat line in a single game since [[Shaquille O'Neal]] in 1992–93.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151121/NYKHOU/gameinfo.html|title=Porzingis leads Knicks beat Rockets for 4th straight win|work=NBA.com|date=21 November 2015|accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref>

He became the first rookie to reach those totals since [[Tim Duncan]] in 1998.<ref name=rom1>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/2015/news/12/03/porzingis-towns-rookies-of-the-month/|title=Porzingis, Towns named Rookies of the Month|work=NBA.com|date=3 December 2015|accessdate=7 December 2015}}</ref> On 3 December 2015, he was named Eastern Conference Rookie of the Month for games played in October and November. He ranked third among all rookies in scoring (13.7 ppg) and was second in rebounding (9.3 rpg) and blocked shots (1.89 bpg) for October and November.<ref name="rom1" /> He went on to claim Eastern Conference Rookie of the Month honours for December and January as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/knicks/kristaps-porzingis-named-decembers-eastern-conference-rookie-month|title=Kristaps Porzingis Named December's Eastern Conference Rookie of the Month|work=NBA.com|date=4 January 2016|accessdate=12 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/knicks/news/kristaps-porzingis-named-january-eastern-conference-rookie-month|title=Kristaps Porzingis Named January Eastern Conference Rookie of the Month|work=NBA.com|date=2 February 2016|accessdate=2 February 2016}}</ref> On 12 February 2016, he scored 30 points for Team World in the [[Rising Stars Challenge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20160212/USAWLD/gameinfo.html|title=USA vs World|work=NBA.com|date=12 February 2016|accessdate=12 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FZ_hlfVTF_Y|title=Kristaps Porzingis Drops 30 in Rising Stars Challenge|work=YouTube.com|date=12 February 2016|accessdate=12 February 2016}}</ref> On 23 March 2016, he tied a career high with 29 points and grabbed 10 rebounds in a 115–107 win over the [[Chicago Bulls]]. He was one point short of becoming the first rookie since [[Patrick Ewing]] to put up 30 points and 10 rebounds in one game for the Knicks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20160323/NYKCHI/gameinfo.html|title=Porzingis ties career high with 29, Knicks top Bulls 115–107|work=NBA.com|date=23 March 2016|accessdate=24 March 2016}}</ref>

Porziņģis appeared in 72 of the Knicks' 82 games in 2015–16, missing the final seven games of the season due to a right shoulder strain.<ref>{{cite web|last=Berman|first=Marc|url=https://nypost.com/2016/04/12/kristaps-porzingis-falling-in-line-with-knicks-plans-for-big-offseason/|title=Kristaps Porzingis falling in line with Knicks' plans for 'big offseason'|work=NYPost.com|date=12 April 2016|accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref> He finished with averages of 14.3 points, 7.3 rebounds, 1.3 assists and 1.9 blocks per game. Porziņģis finished second in the [[NBA Rookie of the Year Award]] voting behind winner [[Karl-Anthony Towns]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/2016/news/05/16/karl-anthony-towns-rookie-of-the-year-2016-ap/index.html|title=Timberwolves' Towns is unanimous Kia Rookie of the Year pick|work=NBA.com|date=16 May 2016|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> and earned [[NBA All-Rookie Team|NBA All-Rookie First Team]] honors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/2016/news/05/19/2015-16-all-rookie-first-and-second-teams-karl-anthony-towns-kristaps-porzingis-devin-booker-nikola-jokic-jahlil-okafor/|title=Wolves' Towns, Knicks' Porzingis lead 2015–16 NBA All-Rookie teams|work=NBA.com|date=19 May 2016|accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref>

====2016–18: Rise to stardom====
On 16 November 2016, Porziņģis scored a career-high 35 points in a 105–102 win over the [[Detroit Pistons]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400899612|title=Porzingis scores career-high 35, Knicks top Pistons 105–102|work=ESPN.com|date=16 November 2016|accessdate=16 November 2016}}</ref> On 11 December 2016, he recorded 26 points, 12 rebounds and a career high-tying seven blocks in a 118–112 win over the [[Los Angeles Lakers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400899802|title=Porzingis, Rose lead Knicks past slumping Lakers, 118–112|work=ESPN.com|date=11 December 2016|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> On 19 January 2017, he came off the bench for the first time in his NBA career after returning from a four-game absence due to a sore left Achilles tendon. He subsequently scored 15 points in a 113–110 loss to the [[Washington Wizards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400900059|title=Wall has 29 points, 13 assists as Wizards top Knicks 113–110|work=ESPN.com|date=19 January 2017|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> During the [[2017 NBA All-Star Game#All-Star Weekend|2017 All-Star Weekend]], Porziņģis played for Team World in the [[Rising Stars Challenge]] and won the [[Skills Challenge]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Dwyer|first=Kelly|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/kristaps-porzingis-takes-the-nbas-skills-challenge-as-the-bigs-rule-again-020145794.html|title=Kristaps Porzingis takes the NBA's Skills Challenge, as the 'Bigs' rule again|work=Yahoo.com|date=18 February 2017|accessdate=18 February 2017}}</ref>

In the Knicks' season opener the following season, on 19 October 2017, Porziņģis had 31 points and 12 rebounds in a 105–84 loss to the [[Oklahoma City Thunder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974441|title=Thunder top Knicks 105–84 in OKC debuts for George, Anthony|work=ESPN.com|date=19 October 2017|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref> On 30 October 2017, he scored a career-high 38 points in a 116–110 win over the [[Denver Nuggets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974845|title=Porzingis' career night lifts Knicks to 116–110 over Nuggets|work=ESPN.com|date=30 October 2017|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> Less than a week later, on 5 November, Porziņģis set a new career high with 40 points in a 108–101 win over the [[Indiana Pacers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974893|title=Porzingis pours in 40, Knicks come from 19 down, beat Pacers|work=ESPN.com|date=5 November 2017|accessdate=5 November 2017}}</ref> Porziņģis was subsequently named Eastern Conference Player of the Week for games played from Monday, 30 October through Sunday, 5 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://basketball.realgm.com/wiretap/247972/Kristaps-Porzingis-James-Harden-Named-Players-Of-The-Week|title=Kristaps Porzingis, James Harden Named Players Of The Week|work=RealGM.com|date=6 November 2017|accessdate=6 November 2017}}</ref> Porziņģis would record the best start to a season for Knicks player, earning 300 points through 10 games, two more than [[Bernard King]] had to open the 1984–85 season,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400974903|title=Porzingis hits tiebreaking 3, Knicks beat Hornets 118–113|work=ESPN.com|date=7 November 2017|accessdate=7 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400975150|title=Porzingis, Beasley help Knicks edge Lakers 113–109 in OT|work=ESPN.com|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref> and his performances continued, where, on 23 January 2018, he was named an Eastern Conference All-Star reserve.<ref>{{cite web|last=Begley|first=Ian|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/22191981/kristaps-porzingis-karl-anthony-towns-victor-oladipo-first-nba-all-stars-reserves-announced|title=Kristaps Porzingis and Karl-Anthony Towns among All-Star reserves|work=ESPN.com|date=23 January 2018|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>

However, on 6 February 2018, in a 103–89 loss to the [[Milwaukee Bucks]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400975547|title=Giannis dunks over Knicks, who lose Porzingis to knee injury|work=ESPN.com|date=6 February 2018|accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref> Porziņģis tore his left ACL.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=NY_KnicksPR|number=961086441508962310 |date=6 February 2018|title=Medical Update: An MRI confirmed that Kristaps Porzingis tore the ACL in his left knee.}}</ref> He was subsequently ruled out for the rest of the season.

====2018–19: Injury and recovery====
In October 2018, the Knicks decided against signing Porziņģis to a rookie extension, a move that will give New York an extra $10 million in cap space in the summer of 2019 while making Porziņģis a restricted free agent in the offseason.<ref>{{cite web|last=Begley|first=Ian|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/24992313/new-york-knicks-decline-sign-kristaps-porzingis-rookie-extension-deadline|title=Knicks to wait until summer to negotiate Kristaps Porzingis extension|work=ESPN.com|date=15 October 2018|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref> Due to recovering from his ACL injury, Porziņģis did not play for the Knicks to begin the 2018–19 season.

===Dallas Mavericks===
On 31 January 2019, after a meeting with the Knicks left franchise officials with the impression that he wanted to be traded,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/25893669|title=Kristaps Porzingis concerned about Knicks' direction, wants to be traded|work=ESPN.com|date=31 January 2019|accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref> Porziņģis was traded alongside [[Trey Burke]], [[Courtney Lee]] and [[Tim Hardaway Jr.]] to the [[Dallas Mavericks]] in exchange for [[DeAndre Jordan]], [[Wesley Matthews]], [[Dennis Smith Jr.]], an unprotected 2021 first-round draft pick, and an additional top-ten protected 2023 first round draft pick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mavs.com/mavericks-acquire-all-star-kristaps-porzingis-tim-hardaway-jr-courtney-lee-and-trey-burke-in-trade-with-knicks/|title=Mavericks acquire All-Star Kristaps Porzingis, Tim Hardaway Jr., Courtney Lee, and Trey Burke in trade with Knicks|work=Mavs.com|date=31 January 2019|accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lovell|first=Blake|url=https://clutchpoints.com/mavs-news-dallas-also-sending-2021-unprotected-first-rounder-2023-protected-pick-to-knicks-kristaps-porzingis-trade/|title=REPORT: Mavs also sending 2021 unprotected first rounder, 2023 protected picks to Knicks in Kristaps Porzingis trade|work=clutchpoints.com|date=31 January 2019|accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref> He sat out the remainder of the 2018–19 season, healing from his ACL injury. On 12 July, Porziņģis agreed to re-sign with the Mavericks on a five-year maximum contract worth $158 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mavs.com/porzingis-mavericks-make-it-official-let-the-new-era-begin/|title=Porzingis, Mavericks make it official; let the new era begin|website=Dallas Mavericks|access-date=12 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Porziņģis signs 158 million dollar deal with Dallas Mavericks |url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/culture/sport/porzingis-signs-158-million-dollar-deal-with-dallas-mavericks.a325641/ |accessdate=16 July 2019 |work=eng.lsm.lv |agency=LETA |publisher=[[Public Broadcasting of Latvia|Latvian Public Broadcasting]] |date=15 July 2019}}</ref>

==National team career==
Porziņģis played with the [[Latvia national basketball team|Latvian youth team]] and was selected in the [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship]] All-Tournament Team.

In 2015, Porziņģis was named the [[Latvian Sportspersonality of the year|Latvian Rising Star of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diena.lv/sports/basketbols/porzingis-nosaukts-par-latvijas-sporta-gada-uzlecoso-zvaigzni-14123984|title=Porziņģis nosaukts par Latvijas sporta gada uzlecošo zvaigzni|author=LETA|date=23 December 2015|publisher=Diena.lv|language=Latvian|accessdate=23 December 2015}}</ref>

In 2017, Porziņģis played for Latvia at [[EuroBasket 2017]], where he averaged 23.6 points per game (ranked 3rd), 5.9 rebounds per game (ranked 19th) and 1.9 blocks per game (ranked 1st).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/Kristaps-Porzingis|title=Kristaps PORZINGIS|work=fiba.basketball|accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref> Latvia was eliminated in the quarterfinals by [[Slovenia national basketball team|Slovenia]], losing 103–97.

==Player profile==
{{quote box
| quote="He's a guy I've always looked up to. It's not fair for me to be compared to a legend like him."
| source=—Porziņģis on Dirk Nowitzki, August 2017<ref name="Porziņģis-Nowitzki" />
| width=20em
| align=right}}
Porziņģis has been compared to [[Dirk Nowitzki]], with the pair having both been groomed in Europe before entering the NBA. Both Porziņģis and Nowitzki are seven-foot-plus players who are comfortable anywhere on the front line and can both shoot from the outside.<ref name=Porziņģis-Nowitzki>{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Shaun|url=http://www.nba.com/article/2017/08/04/kristaps-porzingis-dirk-nowitzki-bond-during-nba-africa-game-week|title=Kristaps Porzingis, Dirk Nowitzki strengthen friendship at NBA Africa|work=NBA.com|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref> During his rookie season, [[Kevin Durant]] dubbed Porziņģis a basketball "unicorn" because of his rare combination of talents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/nba/2016/01/26/thunder-knicks-kevin-durant-kristaps-porzingis-baskeball-unicorn|title=Kevin Durant calls Kristaps Porzingis a basketball 'unicorn'|work=SI.com|date=26 January 2016|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref> In January 2018, Porziņģis was averaging 19 shot attempts per game for the Knicks, the most ever by a player his size (the only players {{cvt|7|ft|3|in}} or taller to average 15 field goal attempts per game were [[Ralph Sampson]] and [[Yao Ming]]). Due to his height and mobility, Porziņģis is able to shoot over any defender, with his sheer size and high volume creating a unique advantage shared by no other player in the league.<ref>{{cite web|last=Adams|first=Micah|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/22259303/kristaps-porzingis-uses-height-unlike-other-player-nba|title=Porzingis can shoot over anyone, and that might be a problem|work=ESPN.com|date=30 January 2018|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref>

